5:
And now, you know the whole story.
What Stella felt from Glaives was
merely the mask he wearsâ€”
8:
He dons the guise of a strong father
figure, but poke enough holes in the
mask and the sensitive man
beneath becomes clear.
11:
Leon said somethin' about that, too.
When one of his companions died,
that man was the only one worried
about the bereaved family.
15:
It was tough having to sift through
all the complaints about his son's
education, or his womanizing...
among others.
18:
In the end, we saw neither hide nor
hair of a spy in the whole bunch.
Perhaps we could have loosened
the net up a bit...
23:
The most important thing is that no
one was harmed. Good work,
everyone!
27: Hell yeah! Y'know what that means!
41:
Whoa, whoa, WHOA! Are you sure we
need an entire venue to ourselves?!
45:
Well... When people heard there'd be
a second party, they simply rushed
to sign up...
49:
Hahaha... It's almost like a wedding
reception.
59:
Looks like there were a LOT of people
itching to see your outfits. I think
Marina must've signed up twice!
63:
In that case, why not a banquet to
honor all the people of Starview
Village?
68:
Gotta be careful there... Can't have
the guest of honor pass out too
early into the party.
71:
I'm talkin' about the liquor. You
might wanna go easy at first. Take it
slow...
75:
Hmph... You underestimate me,
Nimbus. I have prepared for this day
for quite some time!
87:
Looks like Nimbus was right to
worry...
92:
Curse this body... If I was... my old
self, this would be nothing!
96: But for now... I have this!
100:
Drinky Drunky Detox Delight? That's
one of Renoir's potions!
105:
She talked about enzymes and the
like... Anyway, it seems safe! Now... I
shall place my trust in her!
108:
You're really THAT desperate to keep
drinking?
113:
All right! Nimbus! Selgir! The real
battle begins now!
118:
I can't say I've ever seen Light in
such a state before...
127: Heh-heh. I... did it! Two whole pints...
130: Is drinking really all that fun?
134:
Indeed! It was... One of the simple
pleasures of being human.
139:
I guess it's no surprise, but... you
really miss your old self, huh?
143:
I do... Being the Champion is truly an
honor, but I can feel the differences.
146:
For example, I have less of a drive to
find a woman...
149:
What, surprised? I'll have you know
that even I have spent my share of
restless nights, wrestling with
feelings of infatuation.
153:
I, I see... But, you know? Maybe not
having to worry about that isn't such
a bad thing...
156:
S-sorry, that came out wrong! Just
that... at least you don't wind up
making a fool of yourself, right?
168:
I just recalled Shakari saying
something similar once...
171:
She spoke of love and intimacy as
simply being animalistic
behaviorâ€”how she would never
succumb to such things.
176:
Well, you two seem to be having an
interesting conversation.
187:
Whatever is the matter? I just came
over hoping to hear another one of
Shakari's tales.
195:
O-oh. Well, I fear that was really all
there was to it. I remember the day...
It had been some time since I had
last seen Princess Lily...
197:
Shakari suddenly became wildly
upset and spat those words at me.
All I could do was laugh and ask
what made her so angry.
201: Awww... I feel sorry for her.
204:
Shakari was... like a little sister to
you, was she not?
208:
Indeed... I thought of her as dearly
as my own family...
218:
There are monsters in this forest...
Where are you, Shakari?!
254:
I believed I had been blessed with
this power. I left the village a year
after that, though I quarreled terribly
with my father...
257:
Only now, do I understand... It was
love. They loved me.
260:
...I'd be hard-pressed to say that all
of the pain and partings have been
for the better.
263:
But still, I am grateful. These
experiences have shaped my path
and led me to meet all of you, have
they not?
270: But that doesn't mean it's over.
273:
Your journey, I mean. You still want
to return to being human, right?
There's no reason to give up on that
goal just yet!
278:
If you're gonna slap a god in the
face, getting your old body back
should be a piece of cake.
281:
'Sides, I hear you've got "desires" just
like the rest of us, eh?
285:
Yet another pair of eavesdropping
ears... You are not wrong, though.
288:
The life of the Champion is behind
me. Perhaps I should look into
becoming a pirate next?
